"title": "Being a drifter",
"URL": "https://timtianchen.wordpress.com/2017/04/15/being-a-drifter/",
"short_URL": "https://wp.me/p7HHqt-1k",
"content": "\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Things that an academic and a drifter have in common:</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Travel and live in many places</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Bordering on homelessness</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Eat whatever he/she sees</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Live in a metaphorical cardboard on a good day</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Things that we differ, drifters can decide where they drift to. Academics are basically grasping on that plank of wood for dear life, and gets carried wherever the stream decides.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">p.s. the image is the cover of a music cd</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">p.p.s. I am going to California for the summer, thus continuing the drift.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">p.p.p.s. Fun fact, drifting is actually one of the first examples they use to teach calculus.</p>\n",
"excerpt": "<p>Things that an academic and a drifter have in common: Travel and live in many places Bordering on homelessness Eat whatever he/she sees Live in a metaphorical cardboard on a good day Things that we differ, drifters can decide where they drift to. Academics are basically grasping on that plank of wood for dear life, [&hellip;]</p>\n",
